<div class="text-wrap">
<h3>Takeaways</h3>
<h6>A visitor doesn't need to understand everything about the product.</h6>
<p>
  They
  just need enough to understand and remember what your product is and
  how the could benefit from it.
</p>
<h6>Keep the copy short and sweet.</h6>
<p>
  Visitors aren't likely to spend long reading
  the text on your site.
</p>
<h6>Talk like your customers.</h6>
<p>
  In your marketing copy, use vocabulary that your customers use. They'll
  easily understand and relate to your product.
</p>
<h6>Test the comprehension of your graphics!</h6>
<p>
  Most of our early graphics
  were clever by our standards but confusing to people outside of the
  company.
</p>
<h6>Contrast the old way with the new way.</h6>
<p>
  Contrasting the old way of doing things with the new way of doing
  things is a very quick and compelling way to communicate the value of
  something.
</p>
